[MISC French] far-left killer leaves jail 
[LOC ENSISHEIM] , [LOC France] , April 14 , 2010 ( AFP ) - 
A former militant of the [MISC French] far-left group [ORG Action Directe] , [PER Georges Cipriani] , left prison on parole on Wednesday after 23 years behind bars for two high-profile murders . 
A policeman at the scene confirmed to [ORG AFP] the identity of [PER Cipriani] , 59 , who left the prison in [LOC Ensisheim] in northeastern [LOC France] wearing a leather jacket and with long white hair . 
[PER Cipriani] was one of four members of [ORG Action Directe] sentenced to life in prison for the murder of [ORG Renault] chief [PER George Besse] in 1986 and the head of government arms sales [PER Rene Audran] a year earlier . 
The four included two women , [PER Joelle Aubron] who died of lung cancer in 2006 and [PER Nathalie Menignon] , who was paroled in 2008 . 
A fourth member , [PER Jean-Marc Rouillan] , remains behind bars . 
[PER Cipriani] left [LOC Ensisheim] in a police vehicle bound for an open prison near [LOC Strasbourg] where the police officer said he was due to do community service including working at a food bank as part of his parole . 
[LOC China] president urges child safety after school killings 
[LOC Beijing] , June 1 , 2010 ( AFP ) - 
[MISC Chinese] President [PER Hu Jintao] has called on the entire nation to do more to ensure the safety of children , state press said Tuesday , in comments that follow a spate of grisly school killings . 
" The entire society must pay importance to the safety of children and do everything to safeguard our motherland 's next generation , " the [ORG People 's Daily] quoted [PER Hu] as saying . 
[PER Hu] was speaking Monday as he toured a [LOC Beijing] exhibit on transport and building safety with a group of schoolchildren on the eve of [MISC International Children 's Day] , the report said . 
His remarks come after a spate of bloody school attacks around [LOC China] since late March which have left 17 people dead , including 15 students , and scores injured . 
Experts say the senseless assaults reveal a [LOC China] struggling to come to grips with rapid social change following decades of booming economic growth . 
On Sunday , a 47-year-old unemployed man was executed for carrying out an assault on 32 people , mostly small children , at a kindergarten in eastern [LOC China] in April . 
The man , [PER Xu Yuyuan] , wielded a knife usually used to slaughter pigs . 
[PER Xu] , who was sentenced to death on May 15 , told the court his motive was to vent his rage against society after losing money gambling and in business dealings , and suffering setbacks in his personal life . 
In late April , a former doctor who stabbed eight schoolchildren to death in a March school attack was executed . 
Two other school assailants have committed suicide . 
Premier [PER Wen Jiabao] said last month that long-standing social concerns including joblessness and a gaping rich-poor divide were partially to blame for the string of attacks . 
" We need to resolve the deep-seated causes that have resulted in these problems , " [PER Wen] said in an interview with [MISC Hong Kong-based Phoenix Television] . 
" This includes handling social contradictions , resolving disputes and strengthening mediation at the grassroots level . " 
Gadhafi attacks [LOC US] in speech in [LOC Italy] 
[LOC ROME] 2009-06-11 13:34:38 [ORG UTC] 
[MISC Libyan] leader [PER Moammar Gadhafi] on Thursday urged the world to understand what motivates terrorists , and likened the 1986 [LOC U.S.] strikes on [LOC Libya] to [PER Osama bin Laden] 's terror attacks . 
[PER Gadhafi] , who was long accused of sponsoring terrorism , got tepid applause from the [MISC Italian] lawmakers he addressed on the second day of a trip to [LOC Italy] , [LOC Libya] 's former colonial ruler . 
" It is not very intelligent to chase terrorists down the [MISC Afghan] mountains or central [LOC Asia] , " [PER Gadhafi] said in the hour-long speech . 
" That 's impossible . 
We must look at their reasons . " 
He called for dialogue with terrorists , saying , " One must talk to the devil , if it brings about a solution . " 
Sarcastically , he asked , " What 's the difference between the [LOC U.S.] airstrikes on our homes and bin [MISC Laden] 's actions ? " 
If anything , he said , bin [MISC Laden] is an outlaw , while the [LOC United States] is a country that should abide by international law . 
Former President [PER Ronald Reagan] ordered airstrikes on [LOC Tripoli] and [LOC Benghazi] in April 1986 after an attack on a disco in [LOC Germany] killed three people , including two [LOC U.S.] servicemen . 
The [MISC Libyans] say the retaliatory attacks killed 41 people , including [PER Gadhafi] 's adopted daughter , and injured 226 others . 
The [MISC Libyan] leader told the lawmakers he was being intentionally provocative " in order to try and understand acts of terrorism . " 
[PER Gadhafi] had long been ostracized by the [LOC West] for sponsoring terrorism , but in recent years sought to emerge from his pariah status by abandoning weapons of mass destruction and renouncing terrorism in 2003 . 
[LOC Libya] has since agreed to pay compensation to the families of the [LOC Berlin] disco victims as well as the families of the victims of the 1988 [ORG Pan Am] 103 bombing over [LOC Lockerbie] , [LOC Scotland] , which killed 270 people , including 189 [MISC Americans] . 
[MISC Libyan] [PER Abdel Basset Ali al-Megrahi] was convicted of blowing up the plane . 
The [LOC United States] restored diplomatic ties with [LOC Libya] in 2006 and removed the [MISC North African] nation from the [ORG State Department] list of countries that sponsor terrorism . 
[PER Gadhafi] 's visit to [LOC Italy] continued that process of emergence from international isolation . 
But it also drew protests , including at [LOC La] [MISC Sapienza] university , where [PER Gadhafi] was addressing a group of few hundred students . 
The speech to lawmakers was likely to raise more controversy . 
He had been set to speak inside the [ORG Italian Senate] , a rare honor for visiting dignitaries . 
But opposition lawmakers balked , forcing the speech to be moved to a palazzo next door . 
[PER Enrico Morando] , a senator of the opposition [ORG Democratic Party] , said [PER Gadhafi] 's presence at the [ORG Senate] would have been a " humiliation of this country 's democratic and republican spirit . " 
" Only those who have the credentials _ in terms of democracy and protection of human rights _ are entitled to speak to Parliament , the inviolable temple of democracy , " he told [ORG La Repubblica] newspaper . 
Human rights organizations and other critics have also denounced a recent deal that allows [LOC Italy] to send immigrants back to [LOC Libya] if they are intercepted at sea . 
They also decried [LOC Libya] 's treatment of the migrants and its poor human rights record . 
Protests intensify in [LOC Bolivia] over gasoline prices 
[LOC LA PAZ] , [LOC Bolivia] 2010-12-31 01:59:04 [ORG UTC] 
Protests against a sharp increase in fuel prices intensified and turned violent in [LOC Bolivia] on Thursday , as thousands of demonstrators demanded President [PER Evo Morales'] government repeal the hike . 
Demonstrators filled the streets in [LOC La Paz] and other cities to protest the higher prices , which were announced suddenly on Sunday , prompting an immediate 73 percent jump in gasoline prices and an 83 percent rise in prices for diesel . 
It also led to rapid increases in transport and food prices in the [MISC Andean] country . 
Some demanded the resignation of [PER Morales] , a close ally of [MISC Venezuelan] President [PER Hugo Chavez] . 
It has been the most unpopular measure of [MISC Morales'] five-year presidency . 
Taxi drivers held a strike that largely paralyzed [LOC La Paz] on Thursday , and protests were also held in the cities of [LOC Cochabamba] , [LOC Santa Cruz] , [LOC Potosi] and [LOC Oruro] . 
The march in the capital began peacefully but clashes with police erupted when demonstrators tried to enter the main plaza where the government palace is located . 
Police used tear gas to disperse the protesters , who hurled stones at officers , the vice president 's office , a union headquarters and two ministry buildings . 
In [LOC El Alto] , neighboring the capital , demonstrators set afire a car and toll booths . 
People lined a bridge while protesters raised fists demanding the measure be repealed . 
Interior Minister [PER Sacha Llorenti] said disturbances in [LOC La Paz] , [LOC El Alto] and [LOC Cochabamba] left 15 police officers injured , two seriously . 
A group of protesters burned a [MISC Venezuelan] flag . 
" We make a call for calm , for tranquility ; there are police on patrol to guarantee security , " [PER Llorenti] told a news conference . 
Fuel prices had been frozen for six years , but the government said it could no longer afford to subsidize them , especially since much is smuggled across the border to neighboring countries . 
Responding to the protests , [MISC Morales'] government has announced steps aimed at mitigating the economic effects _ including 20 percent salary increases for public workers aimed at offsetting higher fuel prices . 
The government also announced new assistance to rice , corn and wheat farmers intended to increase production and bring down prices . 
Demonstrators have called their protest the " gasolinazo . " 
Neighborhood protest leader [PER Claudio Luna] said in [LOC La Paz] that the government 's " message hasn't met the expectations of the population , and for that reason we're going to continue the protests . " 
He said demonstrators want prices lowered back to their former levels . 
Bus drivers have also held sporadic protests this week , demanding the government further increase fares . 
Authorities ordered raises of 60 to 80 percent in public transport fares , but bus drivers argue that isn't enough to offset the higher costs . 
Food prices have also risen 15 percent in subsidized government markets , but that remained much less than in private supermarkets . 
People seeking bargains lined up at a state-run food store in [LOC La Paz] on Thursday . 
[LOC Morales] , meanwhile , said in a news conference that he is inviting advisers from [LOC Paraguay] 's government to help formulate additional measures to lessen the blow of eliminating fuel subsidies . 
