[LOC CAIRO] - Egypt’s new rulers gave new credence to a court case against the ousted president , [PER Mohammed Morsi] , and members of the [ORG Muslim Brotherhood] on Thursday over their escape from prison during the uprising that toppled his predecessor , [PER Hosni Mubarak] . 
The case was transferred from an appeals court to the [ORG State Security] prosecutor for further investigation . 
No charges have been filed as yet . 
Its acceptance by powerful prosecutors follows the arrest of many [ORG Muslim Brotherhood] members and is a new blow to the group by the military-backed government . 
The detentions have been criticized by rights groups and the [LOC Obama] administration , which spent Thursday walking back remarks made early in the day by a [ORG State Department] spokeswoman , [PER Jen Psaki] , seeming to criticize [PER Morsi] as undemocratic and in so doing seeming to validate the military’s move to oust him . 
At her regular [ORG State Department] briefing Thursday , asked about the reactions , [PER Psaki] said she had been “referring to all of the voices that have been - we have heard coming - the millions , I should say , coming from [LOC Egypt] , and how strongly they have voiced their views about his rule . 
But beyond that is up for the [MISC Egyptian] people to determine.” 
