[PER IKE SKELTON] , FORMER CONGRESSMAN FROM [LOC MISSOURI] , DIES AT 81 
[PER Ike Skelton] , a [MISC Democratic] congressman who was ousted in the [MISC Republican] sweep of 2010 after serving his [LOC Missouri] district for more than 30 years , died Monday in [LOC Arlington] , [LOC Va] . 
He was 81 . 
His death was confirmed by the law firm [PER Husch Blackwell] , where [PER Skelton] was a partner . 
He died at [ORG Virginia Hospital Center] after a brief illness , according to a statement from his family . 
[PER Skelton] , who was first elected to the [ORG House] in 1976 , was known as an expert on national defense and served as the chairman of [ORG House Armed Services Committee] from 2007 until leaving office . 
He was re-elected time and time again in a deeply conservative district that stretches from the [LOC Kansas City] suburbs to the [MISC Ozarks] , and he had a long record of supporting two local military institutions: [LOC Fort] [PER Leonard Wood] and [LOC Whiteman] [ORG Air Force Base] , which he secured as the base for the nation’s fleet of B-2 bombers . 
“He led an exemplary life of honor , courage and public service , ” [PER Maurice Watson] , the chairman of [PER Husch Blackwell] , said Monday in a statement . 
“His commitment to our country , the state of [LOC Missouri] and the men and women who serve our nation in the armed services was unsurpassed.” 
[PER Skelton] was a social conservative who supported gun rights , opposed abortion rights and voted against President [PER Barack Obama’s] health care law . 
Before his defeat , he had not received less than 60 percent of the vote since 1982 . 
But that record was not enough to overcome the national tide of [MISC Republicans] elected to the [ORG House] in 2010 . 
Rep. [PER Vicky Hartzler] , the [MISC Republican] who beat [PER Skelton] and still holds the seat , received support from [ORG many Tea Party] members and tied him to Rep. [PER Nancy Pelosi] , [ORG D-Calif.] , then the House speaker . 
[PER Skelton] was born in [LOC Lexington] , [LOC Mo.] , and won his first election in 1956 to become the prosecuting attorney in [ORG Lafayette County] . 
He served in the [LOC Missouri] state [ORG Senate] before entering [ORG Congress] . 
After leaving the [LOC House] , he became a partner at [PER Husch Blackwell] , working in its [LOC Missouri] and [LOC Washington] offices . 
He is survived by his wife , [PER Patricia Martin] , and three sons . 
[PER Scott] rejects Bar 's lists 
[ORG Times/Herald Tallahassee Bureau] 
[LOC TALLAHASSEE] — Gov. [PER Rick Scott] , seeking to bring the court system more in line with his conservative outlook , has repeatedly rejected lists recommended to him by the [ORG Florida Bar of] lawyers seeking to screen candidates for judgeships . 
[PER Scott] has rejected dozens of attorneys the [LOC Bar] has nominated to serve on judicial nominating commissions , created decades ago to professionalize the bench and make merit and qualifications at least as important as political connections . 
" He wants people with humility , " says [MISC Scott’s] chief counsel , [PER Pete Antonacci] , " and he wants judges who will follow the law and not make it up as they go along . " 
[ORG The Bar] said Scott’s two predecessors , [PER Charlie Crist] and [PER Jeb Bush] , never rejected any of its nominees . 
All 26 nominating commissions for the trial and appellate courts and the [ORG Supreme Court] are composed of nine members . 
[PER Scott] appoints five members of his choosing and must appoint four others from lists provided by the [ORG Bar’s Board of Governors] , some of whom are liberal [MISC Democrats] who did not support Scott’s election . 
The governor has rejected the lists 16 times and has never publicly given a reason and is not required to do so . 
[PER Scott] has sent back so many Bar-recommended names that the group keeps a five-page spreadsheet to track them . 
Lawyers who are registered [MISC Democrats] , are aligned with left-leaning groups or who promote themselves as trial lawyers appear to have little hope of gaining the governor’s favor . 
Scott’s list of rejections includes: 
* [PER Benjamin Crump] of [LOC Tallahassee] , a criminal defense lawyer honored by the [ORG NAACP] for his legal advocacy and who is best known for his firm’s representation of the family of [MISC Trayvon] [PER Martin] . 
* [PER Lynn Drysdale] , a consumer protection lawyer with [ORG Jacksonville Area Legal Aid] who has testified before [ORG Congress] in opposition to state laws that allow payday lenders to target military personnel . 
* [PER W.C. Gentry] , a high-profile trial lawyer in [LOC Jacksonville] who was a member of the legal ' 'd ream team’' that successfully sued the tobacco industry in the 1990s . 
A former county school board member , he has generously contributed to [MISC Democratic] candidates and has given money to [MISC Republicans] , too . 
* [PER Tiffany Faddis] , a trial lawyer , board member of the trial bar’s statewide lobbying arm , the [ORG Florida Justice Association] , incoming president of the [ORG Hispanic Bar Association] of [LOC Central Florida] and a registered [MISC Republican] . 
[PER Antonacci] said lawyers with such backgrounds are more likely to have a " living constitution’' view of the law as evolving and ever-changing , which he said is at odds with Scott’s views . 
He said he did not know what the [LOC Florida] Bar’s agenda was in choosing which lawyers to send to [PER Scott] , and defended the practice of rejecting Bar names . 
" The [ORG Florida Bar] is not an accountable organization in any electoral way , " [PER Antonacci] said . 
" The accountability in the process is with the governor . " 
A spokeswoman for the [LOC Bar] , [PER Francine Walker] , said: " The [ORG Florida Bar] respects that the governor can reject nominees it submits . " 
[PER Deirdre Macnab] , president of the [ORG League of Women Voters] of [LOC Florida] , criticized [MISC Scott’s] frequent pattern of rejecting [MISC Bar-supported] lawyers . 
" I believe it’s unprecedented , " [PER Macnab] said . 
" This is a pretty blatant example of politicizing the court , and citizens should be concerned . 
… It’s disheartening . " 
[PER Macnab] serves on a statewide judicial nominating panel for federal judges and was appointed by [LOC U.S.] [MISC Sens.] [PER Bill Nelson] , a [MISC Democrat] , and [PER Marco Rubio] , a [MISC Republican] . 
Former [MISC Republican] state Sen. [PER Alex Villalobos] of [LOC Miami] , president of Democracy at Stake , a bipartisan group that advocates an independent judiciary , said he regretted voting more than a decade ago to weaken the [MISC Bar’s] role in judicial selection . 
Prior to that , the [LOC Bar] had three automatic slots on every [ORG JNC] . 
" That was a mistake , " he said . 
" We’re reaping what we sowed . " 
[PER Antonacci] said the pace of rejections is likely to quicken , because terms of 78 JNC members are scheduled to expire by June . 
All 78 were appointed by Scott’s predecessor and likely 2014 opponent , [PER Crist] . 
Since becoming governor in 2011 , [PER Scott] has appointed more than 100 judges statewide . 
