[PER Béla Biszku] ( age 92 ) , the former [MISC Hungarian] Interior Minister during communism , has been convicted of war crimes . 
A court in [LOC Hungary] has sentenced him to five and a half years in prison . 
The once-eminent pro-Soviet functionary is responsible , according to the indictment , for the death of dozens of [MISC Hungarians] shot dead during the anti-Communist and anti-Soviet uprising in 1956 . 
Biszku was found guilty today of other crimes , including denying the crimes committed during the communist regime . 
In [LOC Hungary] denial of the crimes of communism and Holocaust denial are felonies . 
The former politician may now appeal the verdict . 
Biszku is alleged to have been a member of a commission that ordered the killing of civilians during the protests of 1956 . 
His trial began in mid-March and has attracted a great deal of attention in the [MISC Hungarian] media . 
The ex-minister was able to be convicted on the basis of a law promoted and enforced by the conservative [ORG Fidesz] party of current Prime Minister [PER Viktor Orbán] that says the prosecution of war crimes and crimes against humanity are not subject to time limitations . 
Several thousand people died during the anti-Communist uprising in [LOC Hungary] in 1956 . 
The revolt was drowned in blood by a [ORG Soviet Army] military intervention . 
During the subsequent purges more than 200 people were executed , 22 000 ended up in prison , and 210 00 emigrated . 
" The revolt was drowned in blood by a [ORG Soviet Army] military intervention . " 
