[PER Colson] authored the 1971 memo listing [PER Nixon] 's major political opponents , later known as [PER Nixon] 's [LOC Enemies List] . 
A quip that " [PER Colson] would walk over his own grandmother if necessary " mutated into claims in news stories that [PER Colson] had boasted that he would run over his own grandmother to re-elect [PER Nixon] . 
In a February 13 , 1973 conversation , [PER Colson] told [PER Nixon] that he had always had “a little prejudice.” Plotz reports that [PER Colson] sought to hire [ORG Teamsters] thugs to beat up anti-war demonstrators . 
[PER Colson] also proposed firebombing the [ORG Brookings Institution] and stealing politically damaging documents while firefighters put the fire out . 
[PER Colson] 's voice , from archives from April 1969 , was heard in the 2004 movie Going Upriver deprecating the anti-war efforts of [PER John Kerry] . 
[PER Colson] 's orders were to " destroy the young demagogue before he becomes another [PER Ralph Nader] . " 
In a phone conversation with [PER Nixon] on April 28 , 1971 , [PER Colson] said , " This fellow [PER Kerry] that they had on last week.. . 
