[LOC Vancouver] pot activist [PER Marc Emery] to plead guilty to [LOC U.S.] drug charge 
No hope of avoiding extradition , plea deal made 
[PER Marc Emery] is facing extradition on three drug charges for selling marijuana seeds by mail order to customers in the [LOC U.S] . ( [ORG CBC] ) 
Marijuana activist [PER Marc Emery] says he plans to drop his fight against extradition to the [LOC U.S.] and plead guilty to one charge of drug distribution in a [LOC Seattle] courtroom next month . 
[PER Emery] 's extradition hearing in [LOC Vancouver] was adjourned on Wednesday so his lawyer could negotiate a deal with the [LOC U.S.] district attorney in which [PER Emery] could spend up to eight years in jail for one charge , while two other more serious charges are dropped , he said . 
" I will be making a guilty plea to one count of marijuana distribution this summer , and then when I 'm sentenced the [LOC U.S.] district attorney is going to be asking for five to eight years in a federal [LOC U.S.] penitentiary , " he told [ORG CBC News] on Wednesday . 
After the guilty plea , [PER Emery] expects he will be sentenced in August or September and is hoping he will eventually be transferred to a [MISC Canadian] jail . 
Joint [MISC U.S.-Canada] bust 
This is not the first time the marijuana activist has said his lawyers are cutting a deal with [LOC U.S.] prosecutors . 
In July 2008 , [PER Emery] said he had made a deal in which he would serve a minimum of five years in jail , but he later blamed [MISC Canadian] authorities when the deal fell through . 
The marijuana activist is facing drug charges for selling pot seeds to [LOC U.S.] customers , after his [MISC Vancouver-based] mail order business was busted in a joint operation involving both [LOC U.S.] and [MISC Canadian] law enforcement agencies in 2005 . 
He 's been fighting extradition ever since , but on Wednesday he said he now realizes it 's a fight he 's not going to win . 
" Ultimately my lawyer is convinced that the [MISC Canadian] government has never refused an extradition request from the [LOC United States] and it 's not going to start now , " he said . 
" Sometimes you have to face up to the reality of what 's going to happen , and under this scenario I may be free out of prison in two or three or four years , " he said . 
Without the deal , [PER Emery] said , he would be facing much more time in jail . 
" This is a preferential arrangement to the not-so-good-arrangement that would see me spend 10 , 20 , 30 years in a [LOC U.S.] federal penitentiary , foreseeably the rest of my life , and that doesn't give a person a lot of hope , " he said . 
Prepared to do time 
" The [ORG DA] wants to paint me as a large player providing a lot of marijuana to people , and we'll bring up that it was only seeds and it was totally transparent . 
It was done in [LOC Canada] out in the open for 10 or 12 years , " he told [ORG CBC News] during an interview at the busy downtown [LOC Vancouver] hemp store he still operates . 
" I didn't keep any of the money — $4 million . 
I gave it all away to activist groups around the world , so my motives are unusual , so that does mitigate in sentencing , " said [PER Emery] , who frequently ran in provincial and federal elections as the leader of the [ORG Marijuana Party] . 
But the man who once spent more than two months in a [MISC Canadian] prison for passing a joint to an undercover officer is now preparing for a much longer stay in a [LOC U.S.] prison . 
" You 've got to keep busy in jail . 
You 've got to be reading , in my case writing . 
I'll be learning [MISC Spanish] , [MISC French] . 
You 've got to have projects , " he said . 
